FT  27 MAY 92 / International Company News: US machine tool orders down 9%
as exports lag
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN FRIEDMAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE US machine tools industry suffered a 9.4 per cent decline in orders in
April, compared with the month before, but the level of orders still showed
a recovery against the depressed orders of a year ago, writes Alan Friedman
in New York.
Orders for the industry were Dollars 220m in April, down from Dollars 243m
in March, according to the Association for Manufacturing Technology, a US
machine tool trade organisation. But the orders were 13.6 per cent higher
than the Dollars 193.7m achieved in April 1991.
The industry's main problem is garnering export orders. Export orders were
37.6 per cent lower in April than in the same month last year, while
domestic orders rose by 29.7 per cent year-on-year.
