FT  27 MAY 92 / Perot clears way for tilt at presidency
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JUREK MARTIN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MR Ross Perot will step down next week as chairman and chief executive of
Perot Systems, clearing his way for an independent run at the US presidency.
A formal declaration is expected later next month.
Mr Morton Meyerson, a business associate, will take over the corporate
offices of the computer services company which had revenues of about Dollars
200m (Pounds 112.9m) last year. Mr Perot will remain on the board.
The Texas businessman has so far contributed about Dollars 1.25m to finance
his prospective campaign, including Dollars 850,000 in April alone. He has
said he is willing to spend more than Dollars 100m.
So far his supporters have officially registered him on the presidential
ballot in only seven states, with five more due later this week. But there
seems little doubt that petitions on his behalf will get him on all 50
states, plus the District of Columbia. He had made this a pre-condition for
running for president.
