<HEADLINE>
FT  27 MAY 92 / International Company News: Swissair sells holding in Kuoni
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN RODGER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ZURICH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
SG WARBURG SODITIC, the Geneva subsidiary of the British merchant bank, has
purchased the 35.8 per cent stake in the Swiss travel group Kuoni held by
Swissair, the Swiss national airline, and sold it to European institutional
clients.
Terms were not revealed, but following the announcement of the transaction
the price of Kuoni bearer shares rose SFr1,100 to SFr23,900, valuing the
Swissair stake at SFr119.9m (Dollars 81m).
The sale has been rumoured for some time as part of a Swissair programme to
sell off peripheral activities.
'By pulling out of Kuoni, Swissair is underlining its intention to
concentrate on its core businesses, the transport of people and goods, and
related services,' the airline said.
Mr Luigi De Carlo of Warburg Soditic said that one quarter of the shares
were placed with Swiss institutions. The remainder were placed with
institutional customers elsewhere in Europe.
Warburg's view was that the shares were undervalued and that the wide
distribution of the Swissair stake would raise liquidity and investor
interest. The Kuoni-Hugentobler Foundation still has absolute control of
Kuoni, with a 52.6 per cent voting stake.
</TEXT>
