FT  27 MAY 92 / UK Company News: ICL appoints advisers in run-up to
flotation
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN CANE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ICL, the UK-based computer manufacturer in which Fujitsu of Japan has a
majority stake, has appointed advisers in the run-up to its proposed
flotation on the London stock market.
It said yesterday that it had appointed Schroders as merchant bankers and
Cazenove as lead broker, assisted by Warburg. The search for financial
advisers has been under way since the beginning of the year.
Fujitsu paid Pounds 743m for an 80 per cent stake in ICL two years ago; at
the time it said it would float at least 25 per cent of the company in
London within five years at a minimum price of 225p a share, giving ICL a
tag of not less than Pounds 1.2bn.
