FT  27 MAY 92 / UK Company News: IRG urges bid rejection
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TIM COONE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   DUBLIN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
IRG, the Irish plastic packaging manufacturer, has advised its shareholders
to reject the IPounds 22m (Pounds 20m) bid by Barlo, an Irish radiator
manufacturer.
Mr Brendan O'Kelly, chairman, said the share-exchange bid - 55 Barlo for
every 20 IRG - 'offers IRG shareholders only 40 per cent of the combined
business'. He said that of the combined entity IRG would contribute 79 per
cent of turnover, 54 per cent of pre-tax profits and 51 per cent of net
assets.
'Your board believes this Barlo offer is inadequate and accordingly cannot
recommend that shareholders accept it', he stated.
IRG announced a 23 per cent fall in pre-tax profits from IPounds 2.9m to
IPounds 2.2m, on turnover marginally down to IPounds 55.9m (Pounds 56.4m)
for 1991. Earnings per share fell to 12.2p (16.8p). The dividend is held at
6.2p with a final of 4.45p.
The bid closes on June 4.
</TEXT>
