<HEADLINE>
FT  27 MAY 92 / UK Company News: Jupiter Tyndall's reconstruction plan for
CST
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP COGGAN, Personal Finance Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Jupiter Tyndall, the fund management group which is battling for control of
the Pacific Horizon Investment Trust, has announced proposals for the
reconstruction of CST Emerging Asia, another of the trusts in its stable.
The plan is to issue shareholders with zero coupon convertible unsecured
loan stock for nine-tenths of the nominal value of their existing shares.
CST would then tender for 60 per cent of the zero culs, allowing investors
to liquidate a substantial proportion of their holdings.
It is hoped that this plan would narrow the discount to net assets on which
CST shares trade. SG Warburg has estimated that a package of one share and 9
culs would have a value equivalent to 90 per cent of the trust's net asset
value.
