<HEADLINE>
FT  27 MAY 92 / UK Company News: Pounds 750m ticket tipped for MFI
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JANE FULLER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE BUILD-UP to the planned July flotation of MFI, the furniture group with
heavy debts going back to a 1987 management buy-out, has gathered momentum
with the issuing of new forecasts for profits and potential market value.
County NatWest, which is advising the company on the flotation, estimated
that trading profit for the 12 months to the end of April was Pounds 70m, up
from Pounds 48.6m, and forecast Pounds 100m for this year.
CNW said that if the group were given a rating in line with the stores
sector, its market value would be Pounds 750m.
An important assumption is that the flotation proceeds will reduce the
group's debts of about Pounds 500m to Pounds 100m, giving annualised
interest costs of little more than Pounds 10m. In 1990-91 interest payments
totalled nearly Pounds 80m, sending the group to a pre-tax loss of Pounds
24m.
It took on debt of Pounds 491m in 1987 during the buy-out from Asda which
valued the group at Pounds 718m. Asda retains a 25 per cent stake.
Mr Derek Hunt, chairman, said Pounds 20m was paid off before a refinancing
in August 1989.
Borrowings went back up to Pounds 503m, which is the figure expected in the
April 1992 accounts. Since then a further Pounds 15m has been paid off.
Mr Hunt and other directors, who own 3 per cent of the company, and 350
managers, could gain several million pounds from the flotation, depending on
the value.
MFI, with about 13 per cent of the UK furniture market, has benefited from
the collapse of such rivals as Lowndes Queensway and ELS, while Magnet,
another highly geared buy-out, has run into severe difficulties.
Mr Hunt said MFI had improved its operating margins without raising prices
by increasing efficiency and through turnover growth in the second half of
the year.
CNW estimates sales of Pounds 640m compared with Pounds 620.7m.
Mr Hunt hoped that after the flotation the number of banks involved in
lending money to the group could be reduced from 39 to three.
The pathfinder prospectus and full-year results are expected to be announced
on June 11.
</TEXT>
