required in the restoration of the 17th century Uppark House, a National
Trust property near Petersfield, West Sussex.
The other major contract, a little more unusual, although not unique for
this P&amp;O company, is the fitting out of the 1929 luxury motor yacht Jezebel:
Work on the 248 ft yacht is being carried out for DML(Devonport Management
Ltd) to the designs of yacht designer Jon Bannenberg.
All the main items will be made at Ashby &amp; Horner Joinery's works at
Thurrock and then installed in the yacht at the Devonport Royal Dockyard in
Plymouth over the next 18 months.
