accommodation. This includes the saloon, dining room, library and staterooms
with bathrooms.
The lift interiors and the common areas in the owner and guest accommodation
are also part of the contract.
Ceilings will have veneered perimeters and lacquereed cof fered centres.
Covered fabric panels with special features will adorn the walls.
High quality carpets, timber parquet and marble will be used for the
flooring, either separately or in a combination of all three.
Jezabel is currently in dry dock and has been stripped down to the bare hull
for survey and any repairs needed before the reconstruction starts. Although
she will be fully equipped with modern systems, the vessel's original style
and character will be carefully recreated.
