election. Most voters in her constituency were moved to Mr McLeay's
electorate. It is understood Miss McHugh is determined to get the seat back
from Mr McLeay.
Senator Richardson resigned last week after reports that he might have
supported a relative's shady activity in the Marshall Islands.
He was instrumental in delivering votes to Mr Keating in his leadership
challenge to former Prime Minister Mr Bob Hawke last year. His resignation,
together with an increased budget deficit, threaten whatever political gains
Mr Keating made in the last four months.
Senator Richardson's former position as minister for transport and
communication has been filled by Mr Bob Collins.
