   TAIPEI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Trade between Taiwan and China through Hong Kong surged 37.9 per cent from a
year earlier to Dollars 1.5bn in the first quarter of 1992, Reuter reports
from Taipei.
The Board of Foreign Trade expects business to continue expanding rapidly on
the back of a flow of Taiwanese industrial investment into China.
