Managers, is likely on Thursday to receive the support of his union's
conference for investigating participation in a bid consortium.
The Union of Democratic Mineworkers has already declared its interest in an
employee buy-out. Whether the association joined with the UDM or formed a
separate group, its interest would increase the credibility of a buy-out.
The association would not regard any venture it entered as a management
buy-out, Mr Meads said. 'We want everybody - all employees - in this
together.' The likely sale of British Coal next year has already attracted
the interest of companies. The government indicated in its election
manifesto that at least some shares should go to employees.
