<TEXT>
The chart shows the member currencies of the ERM measured against the
weakest currency in the EMS's narrow 2.25 per cent fluctuation band. In
practice, currencies in the EMS narrow band cannot rise more than 2.25 per
cent from the weakest currency in that part of the system. Sterling, the
Portuguese escudo and the Spanish peseta operate within 6 per cent
fluctuation bands.
