<HEADLINE>
FT  26 MAY 92 / International Capital Markets: National Bank of New Zealand
advances 22%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TERRY HALL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WELLINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
NATIONAL Bank of New Zealand, the fourth largest bank in New Zealand,
unveiled a 22 per cent increase in net profit from NZDollars 67m to
NZDollars 82m (USDollars 44m) for 1991, writes Terry Hall in Wellington.
The bank said it expected to see its strong presence in the corporate and
retail markets continue in the coming year.
Total assets rose 3.7 per cent to NZDollars 7.56bn. Restructuring in the
business sector was reflected in a NZDollars 11m increase to NZDollars 38m
in provisions for bad and doubtful debts.
</TEXT>
