<HEADLINE>
FT  26 MAY 92 / SSC Radisson Diamond arrives in London
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE SSC Radisson Diamond, the world's first twin-hulled cruise ship, arrived
in London yesterday on its maiden voyage from the Rauma shipyard in Finland.
The vessel, the biggest of its kind, docked at Tilbury where it dwarfed tugs
and pleasure cruisers on the Thames. It is to make five week-long cruises in
the Baltic and Mediterranean before returning to its Scandinavian home port.
Operated by Diamond Cruises of Helsinki, the Dollars 125m (Pounds 70m) ship
relies on a revolutionary design which the designers claim is more efficient
than the technology used on the Australian-designed Seacat catamaran
operated on cross-Channel routes.
</TEXT>
