<HEADLINE>
FT  26 MAY 92 / World News in Brief: Montedison
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Montedison, big Italian chemical and agroindustrial concern controlled by
the Ferruzzi family, reported 1991 net profits down 70 per cent to L168bn
(Pounds 76m). The company blamed the drop on the fact that 1990 earnings had
been boosted by the sale of its Enimont stake.
</TEXT>
